<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TEACHER SENTENCED TO 3 YEARS' PROBATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former elementary schoolteacher who admitted he touched the genital areas of 
a clothed student attending his remedial reading course was sentenced Wednesday 
to three years' probation. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Superior Court Judge John Reid imposed the sentence on Allen Gross, 
43, of Pomona, who pleaded guilty to a single felony count of child 
endangerment June 21. 
</P>
<P>
As part of a plea bargain with the district attorney's office, Gross turned in 
his teaching credential and agreed to undergo psychiatric counseling. 
</P>
<P>
Gross also agreed not to have any contact with children unless supervised by 
another adult. 
</P>
<P>
Four misdemeanor child molestation charges and one felony lewd conduct charge 
were dismissed against Gross as part of the plea bargain. 
</P>
<P>
Gross, a former teacher at Malabar Elementary School in East Los Angeles, was 
arrested May 2 on suspicion of molesting five boys ages 9 and 10 who were 
attending his special education remedial reading courses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
