hole and igniting it," said Paula Aliano, department spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
The fire spread along the side of a canyon, skirting several homes before 
engulfing a house about half a mile from where it began, Aliano said. Two 
residents suffered minor injuries, including smoke inhalation, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Their identities were unavailable. 
</P>
<P>
About 80 firefighters extinguished the blaze by 8 p.m., Aliano said. Damage to 
the house and two cars was estimated at $200,000, she said. 
</P>
