<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: NUPTIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KCBS-TV's onscreen twosome, co-anchors Bree Walker and Jim Lampley, have 
reportedly been a twosome offscreen ever since they paired up on Channel 2 in 
October. Now the Herald-Examiner reports that the two have told co-workers that 
they plan to marry as soon as both of their divorces are final. The pair, who 
anchor the 5 and 11 p.m. newscasts Mondays through Thursdays and the 6 and 11 
p.m. segments Sunday, could not be reached for comment. Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
