<P>
KAIFU WINS 46.5% IN JAPAN OPINION POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's new prime minister, Toshiki Kaifu, won 46.5% support in an opinion 
poll, one of the lowest ratings for an incoming premier but far above that for 
his ill-fated predecessor, Sosuke Uno, the newspaper Tokyo Shimbun reported 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Uno started his brief term with only 35.5% support in the polls and resigned 68 
days later, taking responsibility for the Liberal Democratic Party's 
humiliating defeat in July upper house elections and discredited by allegations 
that he paid a geisha for sex. 
</P>
