<P>
1,000 SIGN GROWTH PETITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Venice Town Council members gathered 1,000 signatures Sunday in support of 
their proposal to halt commercial development in Venice for a year while an 
environmental impact report is prepared. 
</P>
<P>
John Haag, who heads the group's moratorium committee, said petitions were 
circulated at the sixth annual Venice Arts and Crafts Festival. The group goal 
is to collect 5,000 signatures to demonstrate community support for the ban to 
6th District Councilwoman Ruth Galanter. 
</P>
<P>
