<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BRENTWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
TENANTS BEAT EXIT DEADLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A developer who evicted nearly all the apartment residents on the north side of 
an entire city block said that most of the tenants have vacated their 
apartments well before the Sept. 1 deadline. 
</P>
<P>
The offer of a $1,000 bonus for leaving by July 31 helped speed the departure 
of about 100 residents, said a spokesman for Bancorp Development, which 
assembled the row of nine small buildings on Kiowa Avenue over the past year 
and a half. Only three tenants are left. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the bonus, tenants were to be paid relocation benefits required 
under city law, including a basic payment of $2,000 each and an additional 
$3,000 for disabled residents, those 62 or older, and parents with minor 
children. 
</P>
<P>
Bancorp Development has yet to decide whether apartments or condominiums will 
be built at the site once the 25-year-old buildings now occupying the north 
side of the block near San Vicente Boulevard are removed, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
