<P>
CITY ACHIEVEMENT AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Monica has received one of five achievement awards for small cities in 
the 10th City Livability Awards of the U. S. Conference of Mayors. The city was 
recognized for making the community a vital contemporary arts center. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica has allocated almost $1 million for the arts since 1982, when the 
arts program was developed. 
</P>
<P>
Among the major projects completed this year is an illuminated gateway over 
Wilshire Boulevard by artist Tony Delap, a large aerial painting of Santa 
Monica at night by artist Peter Alexander for the Santa Monica Airport 
administration building, and six life-size topiary dinosaur fountains by Claude 
and Francois Lalanne for the Third Street Promenade mall. 
</P>
