<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL MEAL PRICES TO RISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica-Malibu Unified School District Board of Education voted Monday 
to increase the price of school lunches this fall to offset an expected 
shortage of government surplus food. 
</P>
<P>
The price of elementary school lunches will rise from $1.35 to $1.50; from 
$1.65 to $1.75 for secondary school lunches, and from $2 to $2.50 for adult 
lunches. Prices for prepaid lunches will remain $1.35 for elementary schools 
and $1.65 for secondary schools. 
</P>
<P>
The district expects a 52% decrease in surplus cheese, fruits and other 
commodities from the U.S. Department of Agriculture, said food-service 
consultant Alita E. Rethmeyer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
