<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOSS ELIMINATES O.C. AT CONNIE MACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Cardinals were eliminated from the Connie Mack World Series 
Wednesday by losing to Cincinnati, 6-3, in Farmington, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
The Cardinals, who finished third in the series and have an overall record of 
31-7, scored twice in the first, but Cincinnati tied it in the bottom of the 
inning and scored three more runs in the second. Cincinnati added another run 
in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
Troy Babbitt, a senior at Western High School last season, hit a solo home run 
in the seventh to give him five for the series, a tournament record. Babbitt 
was 9 for 14 in the series. 
</P>
<P>
Cincinnati plays Dallas tonight in the championship game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
