<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TOURISM/LEISURE TIME; 
</P>
<P>
JOHN WAYNE'S PASSENGER TRAFFIC RISES IN JULY; AIRCRAFT OPERATIONS DECLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Airline passenger traffic in Orange County showed a slight increase of 1.9% 
last month over the same month a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
The passenger traffic count last month was 396,409, compared to 388,836 for 
July, 1988, according to figures just released by John Wayne Airport. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, takeoffs and landings, or total aircraft operations, dropped 
last month to 46,478, a 7.4% decline from the 50,189 recorded in July, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
General aviation activity -- or activity by private, non-commercial aircraft -- 
accounted for 84% of the total aircraft operations in July. That marks a 9.6% 
decrease from the comparable period 12 months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
