<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TOURISM/LEISURE TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Anaheim Hilton and Towers has won the Gold Key Award from Meetings &amp; 
Conventions magazine, a trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
The award, which was given to 75 hotels and resorts, rates properties in food 
and beverage service, reservation handling, guest services, meeting rooms, 
technical support equipment and recreational facilities. 
</P>
<P>
The 1,600-room Anaheim Hilton received a Four Diamond Award by the American 
Automobile Assn. earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
The hotel has also named Robert Sullivan sales manager. Sullivan previously was 
convention sales manager at the New York Hilton and Towers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
