</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No one picked all six winning numbers in Wednesday's $4.9-million Lotto game, 
state lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
There were three tickets with five correct numbers plus the bonus number, each 
worth $466,995. There were 212 tickets with five correct numbers, each worth 
$3,404 to the holders. 
</P>
<P>
There were 11,507 tickets with four winning numbers, worth $57 each, and 
227,943 tickets with three correct numbers, each worth an automatic $5. 
</P>
<P>
Lottery officials said the six-of-six prize pool will roll over to Saturday's 
jackpot, making it worth an estimated $10 million. 
