<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
EASY GOER FAVORED 1-5 IN TRAVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Easy Goer was made the 1-5 early favorite when six horses were entered today 
for Saturday's $1-million Travers for 3-year-olds at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
Easy Goer, winner of the Belmont Stakes and most recently the Whitney at 
Saratoga, will start from the No. 5 post position under his regular rider, Pat 
Day. 
</P>
<P>
Second favorite for the race was Clever Trevor at 5-1, starting from the second 
post position under Don Pettinger. 
</P>
<P>
The field, in position position order with jockeys: Shy Tom, Jose Santos; 
Clever Trevor; Doc's Leader, Bill Fox; Le Voyageur, Randy Romero; Easy Goer, 
and Roi Danzig, Eddie Maple. All starters will carry 126 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
With six going, the value of the race will be $1,088,500; $653,100 will go to 
the winner. Distance is 1 1/4 miles, and post time Saturday is 2:43 p.m. PDT. 
</P>
</TEXT>
